<plot>Through moments of sacrifice and also of joy, elderly Latinos find the courage to forge a new life in the United States. An elderly woman reads a poem from her new found love. A little boy caresses his grandmother's tired face. Octogenarians study for their citizenship test. And a 98-year-old widow dances and prays for two more years of life.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?126773</url></doc>
